HEADWORD: Morass
<hw>Mo*rass"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>marras</ets>, <ets>mareis</ets> (perh. through D.
<ets>moeras</ets>), fr. F. <ets>marais</ets>, prob. from L.
<ets>mare</ets> sea, in LL., any body of water; but perh. influenced by
some German word. See <er>Mere</er> a lake, and cf.
<er>Marsh</er>.]</ety> <def>A tract of soft, wet ground; a marsh; a
fen.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Morass ore</b></col>. <fld>(Min.)</fld> <cd>See <cref>Bog
ore</cref>, under <er>Bog</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

